      "id": "r1",
      "order": 0,
      "text": "The governor of a steam engine took its name from the fact that it governs the engine as a government governs a country. A gov- ernment in a free country is a group of men to whom the people give the power to govern them. In free countries there is government of the people, by the peo- ple, for the good of the people. The government is the instrument by which the country controls itself. In a free country the people can change the government: they can take the power away from one group of men and give it to another. And there is a limit to the powers that any government is given or can take.",
